    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This FD3S is a pristine example of the final evolution of the 13B-REW power plant. It features a meticulously maintained sequential twin-turbocharger system, providing a linear torque curve and seamless transition at 4,500 RPM. The chassis remains incredibly taut, benefiting from the original aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a perfectly balanced 50:50 weight distribution. All critical vacuum lines have been replaced with high-temp silicone, and the Torsen limited-slip differential provides exceptional corner-exit traction. This unit shows impeccable compression across all rotor faces, ensuring the high-revving reliability these rotary legends are known for.",
